               <p>RICHARD RAWLEY I am a <rs id="t18180909-287-viclabel1588" type="occupation">baker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180909-287-victim2017 t18180909-287-viclabel1588"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18180909-287-crimeloc1589">George-street, Spitalfields</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18180909-287-crimeloc1589" type="placeName" value="George-street, Spitalfields"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18180909-287-crimeloc1589" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180909-287-off1586 t18180909-287-crimeloc1589"></join>. On the 24th of June, about half-past nine o'clock in the morning, my child alarmed me, and said there was a man in the first-floor room, I ran up; when I got to the top of the stairs, my street - door was opened, and a person said a man had ran out of my private door with a bundle of linen. I ran out, but lost sight of the person. I sent for an officer, the people said the prisoner was up a passage in the street - we were examining the house, and heard a noise in the street; the officer ran out and took the prisoner. I found my room-door open, and the articles stated in the indictment gone.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180909-287-person2018">
                  THOMAS 
                  REYNOLDS
               <interp inst="t18180909-287-person2018" type="surname" value="REYNOLDS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180909-287-person2018" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180909-287-person2018" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a cheesemonger. I heard of the robbery. I watched outside while Hardy, the constable, searched a house three doors from the prosecutor's. I saw the prisoner come out of another door of the prosecutor's house in Thrall-street, I pursued, and stopped him in Fashion-street, and found the sheet tied round his body, and the rest of the things in a bundle.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180909-287-person2019">
                  THOMAS 
                  HARDY
               <interp inst="t18180909-287-person2019" type="surname" value="HARDY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180909-287-person2019" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180909-287-person2019" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I was searching a house, I heard he had run from another door; I saw him running, and secured him in Fashion-street. I found the bundle on him. He said he broke the door open and took the things out of the room; that he lived by thieving, and if he had his liberty to-morrow, he would thieve again.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I hope I shall be sent abroad for life.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18180909-287-verdict1590" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18180909-287-verdict1590" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 41.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18180909-287-punish1591" type="punishmentDescription">
